               Renew Your Own Library Materials
   The Technical Library is renewing itself and so can you!
   Following is a step-by-step guide to renewing your library material:
    1. From the borrower information page, enter your social security
       number, and log in.
    2. After logging in, confirm your patron profile information.  For
       updates or changes to your profile contact Georgia Teller, Books
       Circulation, at (505) 844-2738
    3. To renew items that are checked out click the "Items Out" button
       along the bottom or the screen.
    4. Check the box in the "renew" column next to those items that you
       would like to renew.  Then click the large "Renew" button on the
       top of the screen.  OR  if you would like to renew all of the items
       you currently have checked out, click the large "Renew All" button
       at the top of the screen to renew everything with one step.
    5. Record the new due dates.
    6. To exit the "Borrow Info" screens click any of the navigation
       button or links at the top of the screen.

   Note you can also view a list of material charged to your account that
   are overdue by clicking the "Overdues, etc." button.
   If you have questions about your account or this procedure please
   contact, Georgia Teller at the Technical Library Books Circulation desk
   at (505) 844-2738 or by email at gatelle@sandia.gov.   For questions
   regarding the loan policy please contact Susan Stinchcomb, at (505)
   845-8493 or by email at sstinch@sandia.gov.


